index_terms: CHICAGO MILWAUKEE ST PAUL PACIFIC RAILROAD
summary: An ordinance authorizing and directing the Board of Public Works to enter into an agreement with the Chicago, Milwaukee & St. Paul Railway Co, a corporation, securing to the City of Seattle the right to install and maintain a 2-inch iron or vitrified clay conduit under and across the tracks and station grounds of the Chicago, Milwaukee & St. Paul Railway Co, at Cedar Falls, and appropriating the sum of Five Dollars ($5.00) in payment therefor.
